caption: I don't wanna roast this place too much but they're really dropping the ball. Last time we bought the wings, they were almost undercooked. I got a bunch of 30 wings for 4 guys. Under normal circumstances we would have devoured them. Almost half went untouched. Barely any season's/ dressings and seemed to be undercooked. Quality lacked a lot. Will be avoiding it in the future
Ok..decent sized sandwich. Bun was kind of dry and the fire sauce wasnt spicy at all.
Ordered on door dash, got buffalo fire and Korean fire, was pretty good and fast delivery.
Average Wings Over. Food came as ordered. The restaurant is closed for dine in right now but I wouldn't either way, kind of dingy.
Nice atmosphere clean place good food a little pricey but well worth it and try to shakes but overall I like it a lot

This was my first and last time getting food from here. We got sandwich combos. They all were missing the lettuce and tomatoes. All the buns were burnt. I got grilled chicken and my daughter got a cheeseburger. The chicken was burnt and the cheeseburger was beyond burnt to the point that it wasn't even edible. Shame on this place for even serving food that disgusting!!!!!

I got the Hanger 1 (which is boneless wings) with crinkle fries and citrus BBQ and Mango Habanero. The food came quick and it was the hottest delivery I have ever gotten from wings. The boneless wings were delicious along with the fries. I am glad they do door-dash now and will be getting delivery again.

Love this place! I always get the sky master and I don't know what they use but it never bothers my stomach and I'm always satisfied!  Tried the sweet chili sauce, it was great (definitely had a lil kick to it) on a recent pick up order. Tenders and waffle fries were super hot and fresh.Recommend, must try

First time ordering from this Wings Over location and I got a drumstick with a broken bone that had turned the meat rotten. I immediately spit it out and couldn’t eat the rest of my meal because I was so disgusted. This wing had clearly gone bad long before it was even cooked, so why did not one person in the kitchen notice the broken bone and say “hey maybe we should throw this one out before it goes out to a customer”? I’ve worked in kitchens before and the rule is always “if it seems even a little suspicious, throw it out”, so I’m very disappointed at the lack of care for food safety. Other Wings Over locations have been fine for me, but this one is clearly not... STAY AWAY!
They offer a vast range of fresh food. I enjoyed eating here. Staff members are always nice, pricing is convenient and the spot is always neat.

Not at all happy with this place. Ordered delivery and it never showed up, so I tried ordering again and the driver told me that they sent him away! Apparently they said “someone else already picked up that order”. I tried calling the restaurant twice and got hung up on both times. This whole process took like 2 hours when they could’ve just rejected the order from the beginning. Also got food here a couple months ago and it was really gross and the seasoning was just piled on like crazy. Definitely not gonna be ordering here for a while
Always have awesome service and fantastic food
First time and last time there. Wings were undercooked and just wasn't a fan

Boneless wings were dry and barely seasoned. I got garlic parmesan and it looked like someone had taken a yellow seasoning shaker and put some seasoning on top and that was it. Like the whole chicken wasn't even coated.  Maybe I should be grateful though because the seasoning itself was nothing like garlic parm. Tasted 100% like chicken ramen seasoning. And I could just buy that myself for much cheaper.  Fries were good.

Forgot my mask for my carryout order asked in the lobby if i could call and pay over the phone and get the order handed to me at the door to go by the mask policy was told immediately no, that I would not be served and was told to leave. Even though the uber eats or grubhub driver before me apparently didn't need a mask and was above the policy or merely gone unnoticed great customer service guys keep up the great work
Always tastes great, made to order. What else can I say but 5 stars!

Picked up from Wings over Lowell twice now. Delicious both times! I had their garlic parmesan dry rub the first time (amazing!) Then the Texas mesquite dry rub, very satisfying meals. Chicken was moist and well seasoned. Only issue, was they forgot to put one of our meals in the bag the first time. But they were very apologetic and included a complimentary drink.
Pretty good wings! Similar quality to Wings Over Worcester. But they forgot the celery, which I was really looking forward to having with the wings! Never had another branch forget it.
Fries were good but chicken.. All orders were burn. Very disappointing! All i could tastes was that!
Wasn't too impressed,but that because the south sat the bar high !
First time and already have an issue with my order, i make a $40 dollars order and looks like $20 dollars order, food was cold too.
The traditional wings are hot and delicious but if you're looking for actual spicy food you won't find it here, but on the bright side they're open late and within walking from  my apartment.
Great wings

I ordered 4 different types of wings at this place, they managed to putt everything in one container where all the flavors mixed ending in my guests not eating any in addition they switched tenders for the special order of plain wings. Waste of $50
My food was a mess. The chicken wings had a foul smell and they were raw when I had instructed them to do it very well done !!! 35$ down the drain !!!!
Best wings I’ve ate so far, also got level 5 hot sauce thinking it was level 4 😭

Nasty!  This was the 3rd time in the past couple of months that I've ordered from here.  First 2 times were pretty good.  Tonight I ordered the lemon pepper boneless wings because of the poster hanging in their window. They looked soo good!  So disappointed...super dry and overcooked. They had the texture of rubber. I tried to call them to tell them this but I was left on hold too long.  I thought maybe it was an off  night but now I see all the negative reviews, many with the same complaint.  More like a pattern rather than an off night. Update: corporate office contact me and refunded my money.  I appreciate that so I will give them another try.

This place can’t get it right. I gave it a few tries because I remember it was the spot in college but it’s awful. June 2nd, 2020, I spent $24 on their wings and I ended up throwing it away after a few bites because it was so dry and chewy. It was worse than eating microwaved frozen food. I was literally starving after not having eaten anything in 8 hours and even then I couldn’t stomach this. Save your money and buy from the frozen food aisle at Market Basket.
Food was good, parking can be interesting if picking up.
They failed to include the celery.

My 23 year old son and 19 year old daughter love this place. I guess I would too if someone else was paying! They are so overpriced it is outrageous. When we go to order this is last place I hope they have in mind! Good food, at extremely unreasonable prices! Shame on them!
I used to love this place. went recently and was very disappointed by the quality

I ordered from here this evening and my order took well over an hour and I was told twice on the app that it was delayed. I called to see what was taking so long and was placed on hold - at midnight on a Monday. I hung up after 5 minutes and called back and spoke to the very same girl who was apparently not too busy to talk to me the second time. I was told my order was ready five minutes ago and the driver was on the way even though the app has not been updated. I am extremely disappointed in both the timeliness of my order and the customer service I received when I called.
Very disappointed. Ordered off of grub hub, Delivery guy ate most of my food.

I offered the Garlic Parm wings and when I went to eat them I was very disappointed they had basically no seasoning at all on them tasted like they were basically plain. Not great

Very rude and took forever to make the wings and didn't put ranch instead of reading the ticket they just through a small thing of blue cheese on a 25 wings order never again I am going there also I asked the girl at the cash register how long is it gonna take to cook so she backed talked to me but when the door dash driver asked she was more than willing to go check for him. Wasted 35 dollars on this visit and really wish I was not super hungry or tired I would have asked for my money back and went somewhere else. But I just moved here and it seemed the only option I had.
Favorite place to get wings! Always really tasty

Won't be coming back after this last order. I would call myself a loyal customer but not anymore. I ordered a large fries and tots to only get a barely filled container. I'm sorry if I can see spaces clear as day and have it seasoned with a sprinkle of seasoning I would have ordered a regular. Never in my life have I ever paid so much for potatoes for the portion I got. The second reason I'll never come back is the order request. Theres no extra charge to get your chicken coated reasonable but if I ask for heavily coated just to ensure its covered this is unacceptable. I ordered 2lbs and it's already expensive but only 2/3 of that chicken was coated. I'm outraged! $60 dollars straight into the trash due to poor quality.
Good drunk food

Funny, friendly guy behind the counter. The food was good. The chicken tenders were a bit on the dry side, but the sandwiches and fries were good.  The flavoring is mostly done with visible crystals, not sauces. I don't have a preference either way, but I thought that I'd note that.
delish

Wow Wings Over Lowell was excellent. The 1/2 pound boneless Kickin wings were excellent. I will definitely be coming back.

Wings were delicious. They were a bit spicy for me, but still worth it. The atmosphere is casual not a fancy setting or anything (and nothing wrong with that). Nice casual place to have some food and chat with your friends.
Terrible service. Walked in, no one in the place. It took them 20 minutes to produce a mediocre cheeseburger. Cashier wasn’t the sharpest tool in the shed either. Never eat there. Yuk.

IF YOU WANT SPEEDY SERVICE CHOOSE ANOTHER PLACE. Tonight was the first time I ordered Wings to be DELIVERED to my home. It took them 1 HOUR AND 52 MINUTES TO ARRIVE. I called twice (as the tracker on the site was not showing me the proper information), the first time I called was 1 HOUR AND 23 MINUTES LATER and was informed that the driver had JUST left the restaurant. I admit the food is tasty (why I gave 2 stars), but the service is unacceptable. The delivery driver arrived and gave no apologies, I had tipped in advance and regret it. Absolutely love this place. Great food, superb staff.
TERRIBLE!!! Service is awful. Whatever a girl says goes. So if you’re tryna watch football this is definitely not the place

Sometimes the wings are perfectly deep fried with a variety of delicious sauces and rubs and sometimes you'll end up with huge, ginormous, undercooked wings that you only want to eat a couple of. So good!

fast service

Delicious!

Wings are okay, I've definitely had better, they're definitely not the biggest and meatiest as they claim but they're decent sized.  Waiting in a line to get to the registration was frustrating as there was 3 employees just standing around while 1 guy worked the register.

Here three times a week. Great wings
Taste good👍👍 Expensive though💰 not sure if it's worth it. I guess it depends on how hungry you are.

Wings are solid here, the important part is that the chicken is good which isn't always the case in wing places. Service is good as well, always pleasant enough to me. Fries are also great although I wish they traveled better as they can sometimes be mushy when they get home.  But rural life going here.
Great wings. Everyone there is so nice and welcoming. Have had a great time everytime I have been there

I used to LOVE ordering from here. When the boneless wings and waffle fries aren’t overcooked, it’s AMAZING.  But I stopped ordering for almost a year because they kept overcooking everything, making it too crispy. My mouth would kill from trying to chew the food.  I ordered again tonight in hopes they may have changed. Same issue. It seems to happen more often at night. Not sure why. Maybe it’s leftovers or something.  I’m giving it two stars instead of one though because like I said before, when they cook the food right, it’s amazing.
Very good chicken variety.  Open late and have public restrooms.

Their delivery is always terrible but you won't get better wings anywhere in the area. Totally worth it if you can drive to pick up your order. Every couple weeks they send me coupons for free fries and occasionally free chicken in their app, which is awesome

If I was just judging the food they would have 5 stars but the prices are so extreme that it makes me angry. I was expecting "Wow!" It was good.

I was conflicted to an extent when writing this review since the aesthetics were not horrible, but sadly the compliments end there. I don’t want to be another mindless bird in the flock and resort to offensive language, or Reductio ad Hitlerum in describing this establishment; although I would say that it was a little Wernher Von Braunish. But not Wernher Von Braun himself, more like a little brother with a considerable lower IQ and none of the accomplishment. (Cheesy Dis Time)  Me: “This Chicken was DRY!” Crowd: “How dry was it?” Me: “It was as DRY as Menopause” Crowd: “Oooooooooooo!” The chicken I ate was so dry and dead, Logan Paul himself came out of the bushes to film me eating it. As someone who is a trained cook, I know there are plenty of ways to cook chicken without killing all of its moisture, and apparently Wings do not know the simplest among these. Now, Here’s me be nice guy… :) Let Me help out all the Patrons to this sad establishment out with a little LifeHack on how to enjoy Wings Over Lowell at home. Step 1: Pull out the Frozen BBQ chicken that has been sitting in your freezer for the past 2 Years. Step2: Cook Chicken immediately 50 degrees higher than what is suggested on the package. Step 3: Take out of oven 5-10 mins late. Congratulations! If you did this correctly, you now can enjoy the horribly dry Wings Over Lowell Chicken in the comfort of your home, and you don't have to waste $10… Yes, $10s on that GARBAGE lol… -Cheers! #bluehanky137

Surprisingly good wings. The wings are of a decent size, they're well cooked and flavorful.  This place is takeout only. I would order from them again, should I ever be in a late night wing craving mood.

This place serves the good wings, boneless wings, ribs, sandwiches and fries for takeout and delivery. Theirs boneless wings (or chicken tenders if you like) are fresh hand breaded not frozen processed junk. Generally I've been the delivery person for a 3 party situation, but as a customer, I can say "not bad". I ordered the Garlic Parmesan Chicken and it was ok. The chicken didn't have a stand out flavor in itself, but I was not mad about buying it. I'm a cook myself, so I understand that even with the flavor dusting on the outside, the wings/chicken needs some seasonings too. Note to cooks...So 4 Stars...
Very good place nice and good food worker's are very polite
The food was good I didn't enjoy the package deals they had I think they need to make it more convenient for the customers

People rating this location badly, I wish you would see the Albany NY location. That's where I live and that location is trash compared to this one. Also, that location doesn't take coupons, or hand out surveys with receipts, so that tells you something right there. This location is clean, well maintained, and the food is delicious.
The boneless chicken is fantastic! The delivery drivers here are all quick and very nice. One of the best fast food chicken places in MA, handsdown.
Best wings around, I just wish the location we're more convenient.

The food is great. If you like your food a little spicy, they got that.. If you like your food so spicy your face will melt off, they got that too.

After waiting 1 hour and 45 minutes for my "40-50 minute delivery" to arrive I called th store to see what the hold up was . They told me the diver will be there any minute. Honestly they are lucky the food is good because the service is cringey and horrific, we just had the two cashiers talk about what kind of coffee they wanted to order from Dunkins, cutting off my girlfriend in the process.The woman then repeated our order three or four times because clearly she was distracted by her colleagues.
